WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:07.071
We're mainly feed lot cowboys.

00:00:08.131 --> 00:00:12.404
Our primary job&nbsp;
is like navigating among different herds

00:00:12.404 --> 00:00:14.540
or move them to different locations.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.751
If they're&nbsp;sick, we doctor them.

00:00:17.751 --> 00:00:23.622
Meet Bruce Wang, a Texas cowboy that was born
and raised in&nbsp;southwest China.

00:00:23.622 --> 00:00:28.227
Bruce first arrived in the&nbsp;US 13 years ago as an international student.

00:00:28.227 --> 00:00:32.431
He&nbsp;has built a new life for himself here in the deep&nbsp;south.

00:00:33.265 --> 00:00:39.267
This is his journey of finding identity&nbsp;
as a Chinese immigrant in today's America.

00:00:46.125 --> 00:00:54.240
Uh right now we're in Smyre, Texas.
I was&nbsp;riding Bill and he's back there chilling&nbsp;

00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:59.619
this morning. Most of the time he, he was&nbsp;
he was a good boy.

00:00:59.619 --> 00:01:08.614
I'm from Yunnan. All right, so we have a lot of minor ethnic groups
that&nbsp;do have the tradition of breeding horses.

00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:18.720
I was drawn to this culture after I came to Texas.&nbsp;
And I began by putting cowboy boots and hat

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:23.272
on myself. But at the same time, I felt&nbsp;
something was lacking, right?

00:01:23.272 --> 00:01:28.080
Like you dress up like a cowboy and you speak like&nbsp;
a cowboy, but you don't do cowboy stuff,&nbsp;right?

00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:32.555
It doesn't make you a full cowboy.
And that&nbsp;was when I decided to say,

00:01:32.555 --> 00:01:37.140
"Hey, maybe I need to go into the cattle industry and
become&nbsp;a full cowboy."

00:01:37.140 --> 00:01:40.384
They look good. They look good.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.982
I came to the States at the age of 20 as an&nbsp;
international student.

00:01:48.982 --> 00:01:54.139
Generally there's a huge decline in in terms of
Chinese student population.

00:01:55.012 --> 00:02:02.914
Maybe I belong to the last wave of Chinese international students
who came here by a large&nbsp;number.

00:02:04.223 --> 00:02:08.802
The number of Chinese students who came to study
in the US last September

00:02:08.802 --> 00:02:15.192
dropped by almost&nbsp;a third from its peak in 2017
amid tightened American immigration rules

00:02:15.192 --> 00:02:17.749
and worsening US China&nbsp;relations.

00:02:18.996 --> 00:02:22.636
Even fewer Chinese students decide to stay after graduation.

00:02:23.634 --> 00:02:28.423
Bruce didn't plan to stay&nbsp;at first, until he met his wife Bethany.

00:02:28.922 --> 00:02:31.310
What are you laughing about? Do you remember?

00:02:31.310 --> 00:02:37.884
I think that&nbsp;was when we kissed. Yeah. Then your sister said, "Gross."

00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:43.577
I just I'm still, honestly, I'm still&nbsp;so amazed that you 
found me from all the way across the world.

00:02:43.577 --> 00:02:45.750
I'm still so amazed. Oh, me&nbsp;too.

00:02:46.248 --> 00:02:52.855
The couple met during their PhD program at Texas Tech University.
They got married two years&nbsp;ago.

00:02:53.230 --> 00:03:00.791
Bethany is also learning Chinese. She hopes to visit Bruce's family
in China once they have&nbsp;saved enough money.

00:03:00.791 --> 00:03:05.653
How do you say I'm Chinese?
- Zhe Shi Zhong Guo, no, that’s China...

00:03:05.653 --> 00:03:09.854
Wo Shi, Zhong Guo Ren.
- Wo Shi, Zhong Guo Ren.

00:03:10.664 --> 00:03:15.633
Today, Bruce and Bethany are&nbsp;invited to
their friend Tracy's new house.

00:03:17.380 --> 00:03:19.741
Thanks for letting us come.
- Of course.

00:03:20.863 --> 00:03:28.548
Tracy first met Bruce 12 years ago when he was working as an
international&nbsp;student advisor at Bruce's university.

00:03:30.855 --> 00:03:32.178
Amen.

00:03:32.552 --> 00:03:38.634
Over the years, he not only guided Bruce&nbsp;
through his immigration journey, but also became a close friend.

00:03:38.634 --> 00:03:42.685
Have you ever used this gun when&nbsp;we've been hunting?
- No, I used the other one.

00:03:42.685 --> 00:03:44.314
The one with like the pump? 
- Right?

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:49.745
We're&nbsp;going to kind of oil all the pieces and kind of clean it up.

00:03:50.555 --> 00:03:58.065
International students are&nbsp;like a very valued members of the American society and that they're our neighbours,

00:03:58.065 --> 00:04:03.170
they're our&nbsp;friends, uh just like many of us who were born here.

00:04:03.170 --> 00:04:09.680
In the 2024 fiscal year, F1 student visa&nbsp;denial rates
surged to a 10-year high.

00:04:10.303 --> 00:04:14.060
Even those already in the US could face visa revocation.

00:04:15.432 --> 00:04:22.272
Bruce considers himself lucky.
He earned his PhD last summer and hopes to stay in Texas.

00:04:23.332 --> 00:04:30.009
The&nbsp;southern parts of the United States sometimes is not represented
very well around the world.

00:04:31.194 --> 00:04:34.045
A lot of&nbsp;folks here, they're hardworking.

00:04:34.045 --> 00:04:42.324
They're just like folks in China, right? Who want to support their&nbsp;
own families and have a reasonably good life.

00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:47.806
China and America right now are in
a competitive&nbsp;relationship.

00:04:47.806 --> 00:04:55.625
Whatever conflicts are going on between the two countries,
and as long as&nbsp;you're willing to listen to their stories,

00:04:55.625 --> 00:04:59.421
they're willing to open up their hearts to you.

00:05:00.730 --> 00:05:05.697
So, I've been here in America for close to 13 years.

00:05:05.697 --> 00:05:07.100
Yeah. So, a good chunk of my life.

00:05:07.910 --> 00:05:10.578
I'd&nbsp;love to stay here since I have a family here.

00:05:10.578 --> 00:05:16.578
But if I have to go back to China,
I won't let&nbsp;go of this cowboy part of me.

00:05:16.578 --> 00:05:18.041
It won't go away.

